  "texts": [
    "This is is done via intensive searches over validation sets, requiring additional labeled samples [61] and incurring computational overhead, which reduces their portability to new tasks.",
    "CLIP-LoRALow-Rank Adaptation (LoRA) [21] models the incremental update of the pre-trained weights as the product of two small matrices, A and B, based on the idea of ''intrinsic rank\" of a downstream task.",
    "For an input x, a hidden state h, and a weight matrix W ∈ R d1×d2, the modified forward pass, following the application of a LoRA module, is:h = Wx + γ∆Wx = Wx + γBAx(6)where A ∈ R r×d2, B ∈ R d1×r, ∆W ∈ R d1×d2 of rank r, with r typically ≪ {d1, d2}, and γ a scaling factor.",
    "Values in A are randomly initialized via Kaiming initialization while B is filled with zeros.",
    "This implies that there is no incremental update before training, and therefore, the output remains unchanged.In the original LoRA paper, the low-rank matrices are applied on the attention matrices of transformer-based architectures [49]."
  ],
